Bring a large #pot of water to the boil then add @salt{1/4%tsp}. Rinse the @brown Basmati rice{1} under water then rapidly boil it for around ~{25%mins}. Once the rice is soft enough to eat, drain it and keep it to the side.

> You need your water to be rapidly bubbling in order to shorten the cooking time.

Peel the @sweet potato{1/2} and chop half of it into (roughly) 2cm chunks. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25}. Cut the @broccoli{1/2} into florets. Roughly chop 3 tbsp of @fresh Thai basil{1/2} leaves.

Heat 2 tsp of @oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick frying pan on medium heat. Once warm, add the @Panang curry paste{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} to develop the flavour. Once it has become fragrant add the @coconut milk{400%ml} and stir.

Add the sweet potato with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Leave to simmer gently for ~{15%mins} on medium-low heat.

Add in the @baby corn{1} and broccoli florets and continue to simmer for ~{5%mins}. The corn should have a little bit of bite left in it when it is cooked.

Stir the Thai basil through the curry along with half the peanuts.

> If you aren't keen on the taste of Thai basil, simply put less in! Taste for seasoning and add a bit more salt if you need to.

Serve your curry on a bed of brown rice and top with your remaining chopped peanuts.

> You can add a bit more chopped basil for garnish too.